SIMPLE: sextile
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sextile
<hw>Sex"tile</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>sextil</ets>, fr. L. <ets>sextus</ets> the sixth, from
<ets>sex</ets> six. See <er>Six</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Astrol.)</fld>
<def>Measured by sixty degrees; fixed or indicated by a distance of
sixty degrees.</def> <rj><au>Glanvill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sextile</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sextile
<hw>Sex"tile</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. aspect
<ets>sextil</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Astrol.)</fld> <def>The aspect or
position of two planets when distant from each other sixty degrees, or
two signs. This position is marked thus: ⟦8star⟧.</def>
<rj><au>Hutton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sextillion</ent>⟦br⟧
